Further info object-82 Value:
Relationships in the home
Vulnerability factors - what else has happened in this boy's life, who experiences similar difficulties, any ACES, any neurodivergence
Precipitating factors - what happened before the difficulties started, who was involved, how did the boy make sense of it; I would want to know how the family are managing this life cycle stage (stories about being a teenager, a growing boy - what happens in relationships, how do people adjust)
Perpetuating - what keeps this going? has the parent had any psychoeducation around supporting a child who experiences anxiety? how is he making sense of being a boy? what has been happening in school / in his friendships
Protective - what has worked well for him before? what is his social capital? what are his interests, attempted solutions and hopes
Protective characteristics - I would want to know about his relationship with his gender, any cultural / religious aspects that might play a role 
Risk - apart from his educational, social and emotional needs not being met, are there any other risks (eating, sleeping, self-harm, suicidality)
